1
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:14,681
[electronic beeping]

2
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,685
[priest, in Ilocano]
In the name of the Father,

3
00:00:18,768 --> 00:00:22,188
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit.

4
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:23,440
[everyone] Amen.

5
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:24,733
[calm music]

6
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,777
The Mass has ended.
You may now go in peace.

7
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:30,071
[all respond in Ilocano] Thanks be to God.

8
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,786
[vehicles revving]

9
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:46,546
‪A JOYFUL WELCOME
‪FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM FOR CHRIST

10
00:00:48,673 --> 00:00:51,843
[tense music]

11
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:16,451
[man on radio, in English] <i>Attention,</i>

12
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:17,494
<i>Team Alupihan.</i>

13
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:19,370
<i>This is Major General Zagala.</i>

14
00:01:20,371 --> 00:01:21,998
<i>A weaponized bioagent,</i>

15
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>with the potential threat</i>
<i>to an entire region,</i>

16
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,168
<i>is moments away</i>

17
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:27,587
<i>from being transferred</i>
<i>to the black market.</i>

18
00:01:30,256 --> 00:01:34,511
<i>Your team is authorized to intercept</i>
<i>and contain it without delay.</i>

19
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:36,846
[action music]

20
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:51,903
[Zagala] <i>Track the exchange,</i>

21
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:53,530
<i>intercept the buyer,</i>

22
00:01:53,613 --> 00:01:54,781
<i>Abel Merelli,</i>

23
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:57,158
<i>and secure every vial.</i>

24
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:58,952
<i>Failure is not an option.</i>

25
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:04,582
[in Italian] My great friend! Welcome!

26
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:11,589
How are you? Is everything fine?

27
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,385
[groans]

28
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:19,973
Go ahead.

29
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:25,186
[inquisitive music]

30
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:47,208
[groans]

31
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:49,502
You are a great friend.

32
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:57,427
[snapping]

33
00:02:57,510 --> 00:03:00,179
Take the money. My friend?

34
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:07,979
[intense music playing]

35
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:18,489
[gentle music]

36
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:28,124
[music fades]

37
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:32,128
[Atoy on radio, in English]
<i>All units, this is Alpha 1.</i>

38
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:35,715
<i>Locked in,</i>
<i>one-seven-point-niner-niner-zero-zero</i>

39
00:03:35,798 --> 00:03:36,758
<i>degrees North.</i>

40
00:03:36,841 --> 00:03:40,845
<i>One-two-zero-point-five-</i>
<i>one-six-zero degrees East.</i>

41
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,349
<i>Weapons cold. Eyes sharp.</i>

42
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:47,143
<i>Move!</i>

43
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,646
[tense music playing]

44
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:41,155
[brazen music playing]

45
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,635
[Atoy on radio, in English]
<i>Target visible in red SUV.</i>

46
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:05,847
<i>The package rides red.</i>

47
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:07,932
<i>I repeat, the package rides red.</i>

48
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,517
<i>Confirm visual. Over.</i>

49
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,977
[brazen music continues]

50
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:01,319
[intense music playing]

51
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:11,204
[in English] All units,
engage, engage, engage, engage!

52
00:06:19,003 --> 00:06:21,172
Go straight ahead! Just keep going!

53
00:06:21,255 --> 00:06:23,424
[brazen music continues]

54
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:48,950
[grunting]

55
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,328
[grunts]

56
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,834
[grunts]

57
00:06:57,917 --> 00:07:01,003
[upbeat music playing]

58
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,422
[in English] Alpha 1, Alpha 1
in pursuit of target.

59
00:07:03,506 --> 00:07:04,715
In pursuit of target.

60
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:11,389
Raptor to Alpha 1.
Two threats down and car secured.

61
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,935
[revving]

62
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,150
[groans]

63
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,452
[brazen music playing]

64
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:35,663
Galo.

65
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,838
[car revving]

66
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:48,718
[shouting]

67
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:53,848
[shouting]

68
00:07:58,352 --> 00:08:00,771
[tires screeching]

69
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,105
[man 1] Hello, sir?

70
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:44,649
They're taking all of us down.
We need backup.

71
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:49,862
[groovy music playing]

72
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:55,159
[in English] Viking to Alpha 1.
Package in custody.

73
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:56,577
Copy.

74
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:59,413
- [brazen music playing]
- [tires screeching]

75
00:09:21,727 --> 00:09:23,062
[grunts]

76
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:25,690
[suspenseful music playing]

77
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:27,567
[Mariñas] Santiago!

78
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:28,901
[Gomez] Enforcement is on the way!

79
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:31,404
- [man 3] Cover me!
- Mariñas, cover us.

80
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:33,030
Cover fire!

81
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:53,009
Reloading!

82
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,072
Gomez, cover fire!

83
00:10:15,156 --> 00:10:16,282
Copy, sir!

84
00:10:23,539 --> 00:10:26,083
[intense music playing]

85
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:33,567
[tense music continues]

86
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:55,756
[exclaiming]

87
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:04,682
[stirring music playing]

88
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:14,525
[groaning]

89
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,697
[groans]

90
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:27,246
- [intense music playing]
- [tires screeching]

91
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:43,554
[tires screeching]

92
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:50,644
[groans]

93
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,484
[groans]

94
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,204
[tense music playing]

95
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:15,669
[Galo on radio] <i>Raptor to Alpha 1!</i>

96
00:13:15,753 --> 00:13:19,006
<i>Need backup now!</i>
<i>I repeat, need backup now!</i>

97
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:23,677
[revving]

98
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:26,138
[goons shouting]

99
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,950
[dramatic music playing]

100
00:13:58,128 --> 00:13:59,296
Galo.

101
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:11,308
[brazen music playing]

102
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,478
Bring out everything you have learned.

103
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:18,023
[grunting and groaning]

104
00:14:35,374 --> 00:14:38,752
[groaning]

105
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:44,425
[brazen music continues]

106
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:50,431
[groans]

107
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,691
[dramatic music playing]

108
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:07,907
Galo!

109
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,160
Galo!

110
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:15,789
Galo!

111
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:18,083
Galo!

112
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:24,089
[Atoy] <i>Medevac! Medevac!</i>

113
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:26,425
<i>All medic, TIA!</i>

114
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:30,471
<i>Requesting immediate assistance.</i>

115
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:33,182
<i>I repeat, all members are TIA!</i>

116
00:15:34,099 --> 00:15:35,225
Galo…!

117
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,901
[somber music playing]

118
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,459
[glum music playing]

119
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:07,591
ISLA COGON
6 MONTHS LATER

120
00:16:26,777 --> 00:16:29,279
[upbeat somber music playing]

121
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:54,865
[rain pattering]

122
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:57,159
[thunder rumbling]

123
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:01,789
[somber music playing]

124
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,023
[thunder crashes]

125
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,761
[thunder crashes]

126
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:09,148
[music concludes]

127
00:19:09,231 --> 00:19:12,734
[boy] Teacher, Dad said I'm going
to attend high school in Manila.

128
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:13,777
[teacher] Do you really want to go there?

129
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,362
Yes. Me too.

130
00:19:15,445 --> 00:19:18,949
I want to study there
and find work as well.

131
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:23,078
My sister said you can make
a lot of money in Manila.

132
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:24,830
But everything there is expensive.

133
00:19:24,913 --> 00:19:26,832
Sure, but the buildings are beautiful,

134
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:29,209
and the malls are huge.

135
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:31,336
That is why the place is polluted
and heavy with traffic.

136
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,130
But Teacher,

137
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:35,257
there's a future waiting for us in Manila.

138
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:37,885
I know my life will change
for the better once I get there.

139
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:40,512
There's nothing wrong with dreaming big,

140
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:44,183
but a quiet, simple life away

141
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:47,144
from Manila's chaos is still better.

142
00:19:47,227 --> 00:19:50,439
Teacher, don't you want us to leave?

143
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:51,607
Of course not.

144
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:55,360
This place would lose its soul with you.

145
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:02,576
Elaine, are you originally from Manila?

146
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,787
I thought you were from Sitio Bawang.

147
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:09,499
No, I just have some friends in Manila.

148
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,376
Ah, okay.

149
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:12,753
[curious music playing]

150
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:14,963
[boy] Teacher!

151
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:16,298
Vilma, the children!

152
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:17,633
What happened? Let's see.

153
00:20:17,716 --> 00:20:19,051
Oh, no!

154
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:21,303
Stay right there!

155
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:23,931
Help! Help!

156
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,515
Someone’s been washed ashore!

157
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:29,144
[Vilma] Sir Domeng, help us!

158
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,230
[tense music]

159
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:34,441
Help! Someone’s been washed ashore!

160
00:20:40,155 --> 00:20:42,366
[Vilma] Sir Domeng, hurry!

161
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:44,284
[Vilma] Carry him!

162
00:20:44,368 --> 00:20:45,327
[heavy breathing]

163
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:48,205
- [man 1] What happened?!
- Someone's been washed ashore!

164
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:51,250
- [man 1] Hurry, help them out!
- Let's help him.

165
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,501
Move faster!

166
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:53,794
[man 1] Come on!

167
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,712
[man 2] Who is he?

168
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:57,214
[heaving]

169
00:20:57,965 --> 00:20:59,049
[man 2] Do you guys know him?

170
00:20:59,132 --> 00:21:00,425
- [man 2] Huh?
- No… No…

171
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,052
[man 1] Lift him up!

172
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:04,388
- [Vilma] Oh, my…
- [man 2] How long has he been out here?

173
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:07,182
- [Vilma] Let's go.
- Okay.

174
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:23,657
[somber music continues]

175
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:28,954
[Domeng] Sir…

176
00:21:29,037 --> 00:21:31,415
You are here on Cogon Island.

177
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:33,125
What's your name, sir?

178
00:21:33,917 --> 00:21:35,377
What happened to you?

179
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,004
How did you wind up here?

180
00:21:39,506 --> 00:21:40,340
Sir…

181
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:41,925
[man 1] He still looks disoriented.

182
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,844
I think he is from Manila.

183
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:45,053
Maybe he is deaf?

184
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:47,431
He might be a drug addict!

185
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:49,474
You guys are not helping!

186
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:52,185
Can't you see how confused he is?!

187
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:53,979
- Sir.
- [man 1] He's awake.

188
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:55,397
Tell us, sir.

189
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:59,234
Do you finally remember who you are,
or where you're from?

190
00:22:12,205 --> 00:22:13,206
Um…

191
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:16,168
[pensive music playing]

192
00:22:16,251 --> 00:22:19,296
Um… I… I don't remember anything.

193
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:21,423
[man 1] Oh, no, Mr. Handsome
is suffering from amnesia.

194
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:22,758
I feel sorry for him.

195
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,552
[man 1] Sir Domeng,
maybe we should call the authorities.

196
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:28,930
For all we know, Mr. Handsome
could be a missing person.

197
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:31,767
No, no, no, don't… Um…

198
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,727
That won't be necessary.

199
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:36,855
I'll probably remember
everything by tomorrow.

200
00:22:37,481 --> 00:22:39,066
[man 2] Just take it easy.

201
00:22:39,816 --> 00:22:41,860
[man 2] It's best
if you get some rest first.

202
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,862
The thing is, though,
you can't stay here for long.

203
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:45,447
A gathering will take place here later.

204
00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:48,158
[Domeng] Alright…

205
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:50,202
Sir, if you don't mind,

206
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:53,038
I have a small hut you can stay in.

207
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:54,664
You can stay there until you feel better.

208
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:57,125
Sir Domeng.

209
00:22:58,251 --> 00:23:00,754
I don't think that's a good idea.
We barely know him.

210
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:04,883
Elaine rents a place
right next to that hut.

211
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:06,468
[Domeng] Come on, Elaine.

212
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:08,929
He looks like a good guy.

213
00:23:09,596 --> 00:23:10,931
You have nothing to worry about, miss.

214
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:12,516
I'm harmless.

215
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:15,644
Elaine, just say yes already.

216
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:17,938
If I had a place, I'd offer it
without a second thought.

217
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,397
Unfortunately, only Sir Domeng has one.

218
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:23,068
[Domeng] Come on, Elaine.
It is just temporary,

219
00:23:23,151 --> 00:23:27,864
just until Mr. Handsome
remembers who he really is.

220
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:31,118
Poor guy.

221
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:35,997
[inquisitive music playing]

222
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:43,588
Here you are.

223
00:23:44,881 --> 00:23:46,675
The place is small, but

224
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:48,301
there is electricity and running water.

225
00:23:51,638 --> 00:23:53,723
[gentle music playing]

226
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:59,229
Ah, the house next door is Elaine's.

227
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:04,192
If you need anything,
don't hesitate to ask her.

228
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:05,735
She's a nice person.

229
00:24:10,198 --> 00:24:12,075
Anyway, I'll go ahead, okay?

230
00:24:12,159 --> 00:24:13,660
- All right.
- [Domeng] I'll leave you to it.

231
00:24:13,743 --> 00:24:14,870
Thank you.

232
00:24:23,879 --> 00:24:25,463
[tense music]

233
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:28,133
[groans]

234
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:29,551
Ouch!

235
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:30,760
Elias?!

236
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:32,387
[groaning]

237
00:24:34,514 --> 00:24:35,348
Hey!

238
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:37,142
- [panting]
- Let go of me! I meant no harm!

239
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:38,518
What did you do to him?!

240
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,395
- [Atoy] Sorry.
- [groaning]

241
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:42,564
- Ouch, that actually hurts.
- [Atoy] I'm sorry about that, man.

242
00:24:42,647 --> 00:24:44,858
[boy] That looked so awesome!

243
00:24:44,941 --> 00:24:46,109
Do you mind teaching us?!

244
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:49,613
Sir Domeng sent me here.
He said you might be needing these.

245
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:53,617
Anyway, I'll be going now.

246
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:55,410
- I'm really sorry.
- I'll go ahead.

247
00:24:56,244 --> 00:24:57,078
[Elias] Let's go.

248
00:24:58,246 --> 00:24:59,289
You scared him to death.

249
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:01,541
Also, how did you manage to do all that?

250
00:25:04,794 --> 00:25:06,880
Who are you, really?

251
00:25:08,173 --> 00:25:09,674
Don't you remember anything at all?

252
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:14,471
Why? Do you really not believe me?

253
00:25:14,554 --> 00:25:16,640
Should I believe you?

254
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:19,726
[somber music continues]

255
00:25:48,129 --> 00:25:49,881
[inquisitive music playing]

256
00:26:02,102 --> 00:26:05,897
[inquisitive music continues]

257
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,746
[indistinct chattering]

258
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:25,208
[boy murmurs]

259
00:26:26,626 --> 00:26:27,502
- Hey, Buddy.
- [boy chatters]

260
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:34,718
What is it?

261
00:26:35,218 --> 00:26:37,220
Do you happen to know who lives there?

262
00:26:39,264 --> 00:26:40,849
In that white house?

263
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:42,267
Mmm-hmm.

264
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:45,145
Sir, a ghost lives there.

265
00:26:45,228 --> 00:26:46,813
Sir, don't listen to him.

266
00:26:46,896 --> 00:26:49,024
We actually have no idea who lives there.

267
00:26:49,607 --> 00:26:53,862
But my mom said whoever lives there
is dating a rich foreigner.

268
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:56,031
Foreigner?

269
00:26:56,531 --> 00:26:58,575
Yes, but he only comes here
once in a while.

270
00:26:58,658 --> 00:27:01,453
And he owns a really fancy boat, sir.

271
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:05,290
He's always giving out
chocolates and candy, too.

272
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:07,917
We're super excited
because he's coming back soon.

273
00:27:08,501 --> 00:27:11,004
He only comes during summer.

274
00:27:11,087 --> 00:27:13,757
And summer is fast approaching.

275
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:16,051
Anyway, sir, why do you ask?
Would you also like to ask for candy?

276
00:27:17,177 --> 00:27:18,178
Hmm.

277
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:19,888
[scoffs]

278
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,057
I just found a hermit crab!

279
00:27:25,268 --> 00:27:28,480
[curious music]

280
00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:37,405
[upbeat sultry music playing]

281
00:27:39,908 --> 00:27:43,578
[sultry music playing]

282
00:27:58,426 --> 00:27:59,260
‪[scoffs]

283
00:28:02,263 --> 00:28:05,725
[sensual music]

284
00:28:18,863 --> 00:28:20,490
Why are you here?

285
00:28:20,573 --> 00:28:22,700
Aren't you supposed
to be resting in your place?

286
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:25,662
I'm just looking for something.

287
00:28:26,746 --> 00:28:29,707
It could be here, at the same place
where I ended up ashore.

288
00:28:31,584 --> 00:28:34,087
[curious music playing]

289
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:48,268
- I'll go ahead.
- Wait a moment.

290
00:28:48,351 --> 00:28:50,353
I think that necklace belongs to me.

291
00:28:52,397 --> 00:28:54,983
But I thought you didn't remember a thing.

292
00:28:56,609 --> 00:28:57,610
I don't.

293
00:28:59,028 --> 00:29:00,280
But…

294
00:29:00,363 --> 00:29:01,698
[curious music playing]

295
00:29:01,781 --> 00:29:06,202
It's like… a memory
just came rushing back…

296
00:29:06,286 --> 00:29:09,706
I'm getting flashes
from when my mom gave me that.

297
00:29:11,082 --> 00:29:12,333
- This?
- Yes.

298
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:15,795
That's impossible…

299
00:29:16,504 --> 00:29:17,714
because this is mine.

300
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:19,758
Mmm.

301
00:29:20,967 --> 00:29:22,302
[chuckles]

302
00:29:22,385 --> 00:29:23,386
Maybe it just looks like it.

303
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:24,637
[curious music continues]

304
00:29:46,242 --> 00:29:48,995
ISLA COGON
DAYCARE CENTER

305
00:29:49,078 --> 00:29:50,663
[indistinct chattering]

306
00:29:57,337 --> 00:29:58,338
[grunts]

307
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:01,508
This is the first time I have seen that.

308
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:03,176
What?

309
00:30:03,259 --> 00:30:05,303
Are you a devotee
of Saint Anthony of Padua?

310
00:30:06,596 --> 00:30:07,597
Ah, are you talking about this?

311
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,932
[Vilma] Yes.

312
00:30:09,015 --> 00:30:10,892
That is Saint Anthony of Padua.

313
00:30:11,726 --> 00:30:16,356
He's the patron saint whom people pray to
for lost things or missing persons.

314
00:30:16,439 --> 00:30:17,357
You didn't know that?

315
00:30:18,441 --> 00:30:19,275
No.

316
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:23,488
I only found this the day
Mr. Amnesia showed up.

317
00:30:23,571 --> 00:30:24,405
Ah…

318
00:30:24,489 --> 00:30:26,825
I think this belongs to him.

319
00:30:26,908 --> 00:30:27,951
[indistinct chattering]

320
00:30:28,034 --> 00:30:29,619
I just never returned it.

321
00:30:29,702 --> 00:30:30,787
You're out of your mind!

322
00:30:30,870 --> 00:30:32,705
Why didn't you give it back?

323
00:30:32,789 --> 00:30:35,375
[chuckles] Just give it back already.

324
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:40,046
It might help him remember who he is
and where he came from, right?

325
00:30:40,129 --> 00:30:43,383
You know, I can't shake
this feeling about that man.

326
00:30:44,467 --> 00:30:46,344
There's something off about him.

327
00:30:46,427 --> 00:30:47,262
Huh?

328
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:49,013
What do you mean?

329
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:55,895
I feel like he's hiding something.

330
00:31:05,405 --> 00:31:09,826
[sultry, curious music playing]

331
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,079
[soft chuckle]

332
00:31:28,261 --> 00:31:29,596
Where is he headed?

333
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,348
[music concludes]

334
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:43,860
[mysterious music]

335
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:09,552
[inquisitive music playing]

336
00:32:42,251 --> 00:32:43,628
[tense music]

337
00:32:47,215 --> 00:32:48,508
[Atoy] Confirmation code.

338
00:32:49,425 --> 00:32:52,470
Zero-zero-six-seven-niner.

339
00:32:52,553 --> 00:32:54,681
Confirm transmission. Over.

340
00:32:54,764 --> 00:32:58,226
[Ranger] Received
and acknowledged at 1300 hours.

341
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,436
Status, Captain.

342
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,230
[Atoy on radio]
<i>I am here now, at Cogon Island.</i>

343
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:04,607
<i>Finally, I identified our target location.</i>

344
00:33:04,691 --> 00:33:06,859
How's the community treating you?

345
00:33:06,943 --> 00:33:08,361
Locals are curious,

346
00:33:08,444 --> 00:33:09,904
yet they're still willing to assist.

347
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:11,531
No hostile movements detected.

348
00:33:11,614 --> 00:33:16,995
I surveyed the perimeter and identified
one modern house on a hill,

349
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:19,247
possibly owned by the wife of the target,

350
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:21,082
with private road access. Over.

351
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:23,668
Good, Captain!

352
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:27,922
FS Karayom is present.

353
00:33:28,006 --> 00:33:29,674
De-brief them quickly.

354
00:33:31,592 --> 00:33:32,927
[Atoy in English] <i>Good morning,</i>
<i>First Strikers.</i>

355
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:35,596
<i>Our main target is Abel Merelli.</i>

356
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:38,349
He's an Italian-Argentinian
businessman and billionaire,

357
00:33:38,433 --> 00:33:43,146
and is the main funder
of the paramilitary group Rogue Crescent.

358
00:33:43,229 --> 00:33:46,983
According to our intel, Rogue Crescent
is waiting for the final funding

359
00:33:47,066 --> 00:33:49,819
from Merelli before attacking
our southern sector

360
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:51,821
within the next few months.

361
00:33:51,904 --> 00:33:54,574
Locals report target's estimated arrival

362
00:33:54,657 --> 00:33:56,325
within the next few weeks.

363
00:33:56,409 --> 00:33:57,869
[Ranger] I'm authorizing deployment

364
00:33:57,952 --> 00:34:00,872
of FS Karayom unit near your location.

365
00:34:00,955 --> 00:34:02,790
They will be on standby.

366
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:03,708
[Atoy] <i>Copy, Sir.</i>

367
00:34:03,791 --> 00:34:06,127
Team, we have to capture Merelli

368
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:07,754
and take down Rogue Crescent.

369
00:34:07,837 --> 00:34:10,965
If we let him slip, the consequences
for us will be severe.

370
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:13,760
[Atoy, in English]
<i>Failure is not an option this time, team.</i>

371
00:34:13,843 --> 00:34:15,428
<i>We owe it to our brothers,</i>

372
00:34:15,511 --> 00:34:18,139
<i>the fallen members</i>
<i>of FS Alupihan in Laoag,</i>

373
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:20,016
<i>where Merelli first got away.</i>

374
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:22,977
Once I get confirmation
of the target's presence,

375
00:34:24,145 --> 00:34:26,981
we proceed with the Bravo protocol.

376
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:28,608
- Copy?
- [team] Copy, Sir!

377
00:34:34,363 --> 00:34:36,324
[music concludes]

378
00:34:39,285 --> 00:34:42,997
[inquisitive music playing]

379
00:34:49,754 --> 00:34:51,172
[breathing heavily]

380
00:34:55,051 --> 00:34:57,804
[inquisitive music continues]

381
00:35:01,015 --> 00:35:03,643
[breathing heavily]

382
00:35:17,281 --> 00:35:19,117
[muffled screams]

383
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,577
[stirring music playing]

384
00:35:28,376 --> 00:35:29,752
[screaming]

385
00:35:31,546 --> 00:35:33,631
[intense music playing]

386
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:43,391
[Elaine] <i>How can I even trust</i>
<i>a complete stranger?</i>

387
00:35:43,474 --> 00:35:44,851
Who are you?!

388
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:46,352
UP NEXT

389
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,022
Atoy?

390
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:56,863
[clamoring]

391
00:35:58,030 --> 00:36:00,575
Baldo… don't even bother.

392
00:36:00,658 --> 00:36:02,368
[man] <i>You disappeared for years,</i>

393
00:36:02,451 --> 00:36:04,453
<i>and now you've come back</i>
<i>just to stir things up?!</i>

394
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:06,372
I want to meet the man himself.

395
00:36:06,455 --> 00:36:08,291
I get it. No name.

396
00:36:08,374 --> 00:36:09,834
I'll just call you The Master Cutter.

397
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:16,841
[electronic beeping]

398
00:36:16,924 --> 00:36:19,760
[music concludes]

399
00:36:19,844 --> 00:36:21,804
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr
